Home (hero, services, CTA booking, quick contact)

About (experience, Saudi background highlight, trust/credibility)

Services (break out: Maintenance, Engine service, Transmission, Suspension, Brakes, Diagnostics, Mobile Repair, Inspections, Rebuilds — each with a short page or anchor section)

Gallery (Before / After photos, video reels)

Book / Contact (form + phone + map + Google Business embed)

Testimonials / Reviews

FAQ (turnaround, pricing policy, mobile service area)

Blog / Build Log (vlog + posts) — optional but important for SEO

Shop (merch/parts later)

Legal / Policies (T&Cs, privacy, payment terms)

Homepage wireframe + content blocks (priority order)

Hero: Big logo (your red muscle car), headline, 1-line subhead, Primary CTA: Book Inspection (form anchor).

Example headline: Elbey Projects — Honest mobile mechanics & engine service in [CITY]

Subhead: Fast diagnostics • Mobile repairs • 15 years of hands-on experience

Why Us (3 bullets): Price, honest, mobile & reliable (short icons)

Top Services (3-5 cards): Brakes, Oil, Diagnostics, Suspension, Mobile Repair (each with CTA)

Quick booking widget: Date, time range, service type, phone, address — fast path to conversion

Gallery highlight: before/after carousel + video thumbnail

Testimonials: 3–5 quotes with star ratings

About snippet + link to full About

Local SEO block: Service areas + Google Business Profile snapshot (makes Google happy)

Footer: contact, hours (24/7 note), social links, small nav, domain/email

Pages: content & length guidance

Services pages: 300–450 words each, with 3 strong photos and a “book now” CTA.

About: 350–600 words — emphasize 15 years in Saudi Arabia + hands-on experience. Give a short human story.

Gallery: visual-first; captions + 1–2 lines context per project.

Blog posts: 600–1,200 words, local keywords (see SEO section).
Keep copy conversational, clear, and slightly confident — no jive, no nonsense.

Booking Form (fields + behavior)

Name, Phone (required), Email (optional), Service needed (dropdown), Preferred date, Preferred time, Address (or pickup/dropoff), Vehicle make/model/year, Short description, Attach photo (optional), How they heard about you (select)

Integrations: send form to client email + webhook to Zapier/Make for SMS reminders + calendar invite. Add admin dashboard for incoming requests.

Consent checkbox: “I agree to receive SMS/calls about my booking.”

Local SEO essentials (non-negotiable)

Create / claim Google Business Profile and keep NAP consistent (Name, Address, Phone). GBP is a must for local search & calls.
