Launch timeline & deliverables (realistic)

I’m giving a timeline so your client stops asking “how’s it coming along” every 12 hours.

Day 0–2: Host + domain setup, Google Business Profile creation.

Day 3–5: Install WP, theme, Elementor, basic security, create homepage + contact page.

Day 6–9: Services pages, booking form wiring, gallery + testimonials, About.

Day 10–12: SEO basics, analytics, Google submission, mobile tweaks.

Day 13–14: QA, client review, revisions, launch.
Total: ~2 weeks for an MVP. If client drags or wants video editing, add time.

Estimated cost (pick a lane)

Budget build (cheap, fast): $600–$900 — basic WP site, off-the-shelf theme, minimal custom work.

Standard pro: $1,200–$2,400 — custom design, gallery, booking workflow, basic SEO.

Full pro + ongoing support: $2,500+ + $40–$120/mo hosting & maintenance.
Be decisive: pick one and sell the value — “I’ll build it clean, teach you the basics, and handle updates for $X/mo.”

