# ELBEY PROJECTS — Website Blueprint & Build Plan

## Big decision (I picked one so you don’t stall)

**Recommendation:** Build with **WordPress + Elementor (or a lightweight theme)** + managed hosting (affordable, reliable).
Why: cheapest to launch, easiest for the customer to update, huge plugin ecosystem for booking/SEO/analytics, and simple maintenance path. If you want a prettier no-code handoff and don’t mind higher monthly costs, Webflow is the alternative — great design control but pricier. ([Zapier][1])

---

## Sitemap (what the site will include)

1. Home (hero, services, CTA booking, quick contact)
2. About (experience, Saudi background highlight, trust/credibility)
3. Services (break out: Maintenance, Engine service, Transmission, Suspension, Brakes, Diagnostics, Mobile Repair, Inspections, Rebuilds — each with a short page or anchor section)
4. Gallery (Before / After photos, video reels)
5. Book / Contact (form + phone + map + Google Business embed)
6. Testimonials / Reviews
7. FAQ (turnaround, pricing policy, mobile service area)
8. Blog / Build Log (vlog + posts) — optional but important for SEO
9. Shop (merch/parts later)
10. Legal / Policies (T&Cs, privacy, payment terms)

---

## Homepage wireframe + content blocks (priority order)

1. **Hero:** Big logo (your red muscle car), headline, 1-line subhead, Primary CTA: **Book Inspection** (form anchor).

   * Example headline: *Elbey Projects — Honest mobile mechanics & engine service in [CITY]*
   * Subhead: *Fast diagnostics • Mobile repairs • 15 years of hands-on experience*
2. **Why Us (3 bullets):** Price, honest, mobile & reliable (short icons)
3. **Top Services (3-5 cards):** Brakes, Oil, Diagnostics, Suspension, Mobile Repair (each with CTA)
4. **Quick booking widget:** Date, time range, service type, phone, address — fast path to conversion
5. **Gallery highlight:** before/after carousel + video thumbnail
6. **Testimonials:** 3–5 quotes with star ratings
7. **About snippet + link to full About**
8. **Local SEO block:** Service areas + Google Business Profile snapshot (makes Google happy)
9. Footer: contact, hours (24/7 note), social links, small nav, domain/email

---

## Pages: content & length guidance

* Services pages: 300–450 words each, with 3 strong photos and a “book now” CTA.
* About: 350–600 words — emphasize 15 years in Saudi Arabia + hands-on experience. Give a short human story.
* Gallery: visual-first; captions + 1–2 lines context per project.
* Blog posts: 600–1,200 words, local keywords (see SEO section).
  Keep copy conversational, clear, and slightly confident — no jive, no nonsense.

---

## Booking Form (fields + behavior)

* Name, Phone (required), Email (optional), Service needed (dropdown), Preferred date, Preferred time, Address (or pickup/dropoff), Vehicle make/model/year, Short description, Attach photo (optional), How they heard about you (select)
* Integrations: send form to client email + webhook to Zapier/Make for SMS reminders + calendar invite. Add admin dashboard for incoming requests.
* Consent checkbox: “I agree to receive SMS/calls about my booking.”

---

## Local SEO essentials (non-negotiable)

* Create / claim **Google Business Profile** and keep NAP consistent (Name, Address, Phone). GBP is a must for local search & calls. ([BabyLoveGrowth][2])
* Create service-area pages (one page per neighborhood/city you serve) — Google likes local pages. ([anatechconsultancy.com][3])
* On-page basics: title tags like “Mechanic in [City] — Elbey Projects | Brakes, Engine Service”; meta descriptions; schema for LocalBusiness and Service.
* Collect reviews and display them; solicit via SMS link after each job. Reviews boost local rankings fast. ([Optimize][4])
* Blog ideas: “How to tell if your suspension is shot”, “What a pre-purchase inspection covers” — target long-tail local queries. ([Tekmetric][5])

---

## Visual & Brand Assets

* Use the red muscle car logo (center stage). Big, bold typeface for headlines — the logo already nails that.
* Color palette: Black background, red accent (#c62828), cream/ivory text for contrast (matches logo vibe).
* Fonts: Strong headline font (condensed sans), readable body font (system sans).
* Photo guidance: shoot clean before/after, 3 angles, close-up of workmanship, mobile repair in action. Add short video reels (30–60s) for IG + site.

---

## Technical stack & integrations (specific)

* **CMS/Build:** WordPress + Elementor (fast builds, easy client edits). Backups + security plugin (Updraft/Jetpack or similar). ([Zapier][1])
* **Hosting:** Managed WordPress hosting (SiteGround, Hostinger, or similar managed hosts). Pick budget vs support based on client needs — SiteGround for support, Hostinger for price. ([Tom's Guide][6])
* **Forms:** Elementor form or WPForms; Zapier/Make webhook for SMS & calendar.
* **Analytics & SEO:** Google Analytics, Google Search Console, Yoast or RankMath.
* **Payments (optional):** Stripe or Square for deposits/parts.
* **Security:** SSL (free via host/Let’s Encrypt), firewall plugin, regular backups.
* **Optional:** Instagram feed / YouTube embed for build videos.

---

## UX notes (conversion-focused)

* Phone number in header clickable for mobile.
* Sticky CTA on mobile: “Book Inspection” (persistent).
* Fast load times: compress images, use CDN via host. Mobile-first design — local customers search from phones. ([Optimize][4])

---

## Accessibility & Legal

* Alt tags for images, contrast checks for text, keyboard navigation for forms.
* Add privacy policy, cookie notice if analytics used, clear cancellation/refund policy.

---

## Launch timeline & deliverables (realistic)

I’m giving a timeline so your client stops asking “how’s it coming along” every 12 hours.

* **Day 0–2:** Host + domain setup, Google Business Profile creation.
* **Day 3–5:** Install WP, theme, Elementor, basic security, create homepage + contact page.
* **Day 6–9:** Services pages, booking form wiring, gallery + testimonials, About.
* **Day 10–12:** SEO basics, analytics, Google submission, mobile tweaks.
* **Day 13–14:** QA, client review, revisions, launch.
  Total: **~2 weeks** for an MVP. If client drags or wants video editing, add time.

---

## Estimated cost (pick a lane)

* **Budget build (cheap, fast):** $600–$900 — basic WP site, off-the-shelf theme, minimal custom work.
* **Standard pro:** $1,200–$2,400 — custom design, gallery, booking workflow, basic SEO.
* **Full pro + ongoing support:** $2,500+ + $40–$120/mo hosting & maintenance.
  Be decisive: pick one and sell the value — “I’ll build it clean, teach you the basics, and handle updates for $X/mo.”

---

## SEO launch checklist (quick)

* Claim Google Business Profile, add photos and hours. ([BabyLoveGrowth][2])
* 5 service pages + 3 city pages. ([anatechconsultancy.com][3])
* Add LocalBusiness schema + Service schema.
* Add contact phone in H1/H2 (visible to Google).
* Start 1 blog per week for 4 weeks to seed long-tail keywords. ([Tekmetric][5])

---

## Example micro-copy (copy you can paste)

**Hero CTA:** Book an inspection — same-day mobile service.
**Service card (Engine Service):** Full diagnostics, filter & fluid checks, belt & sensor inspection. Starts at $X (est). Book now.
**About blur:** *15 years fixing everything from desert trucks in Saudi Arabia to daily drivers here. Elbey Projects is mobile, honest, and built on real skills — not YouTube tutorials.*

